ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is a very good introduction to Probability and Stochastic Processes. It clarifies a lot of concepts introduced in probability theory, concepts that are often not taught very well to students from other fields than applied math.I would recommend this class as a good introduction to any student from a non-math department (physicists or engineers for example) interested in Stochastic processes.
Yes, it is a good intro class.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: More examples that demonstrate applications of stochastic models will be more beneficial for my research.
